kd pf-165dcd23" data-pf-type="Section"><div class="sc-pQQXS iWCqut" style="max-width: 1170px;"><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-5bb0165d pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg:15px; --pf-s-md:15px; --pf-s-sm:15px; --pf-s-xs:15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--undefined"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-52030495" data-pf-type="Column"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-176b0a95"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-7fe86886">Is Meloxicam Safe for Dogs?<br></span></h2><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-oUbqx bgMQOP pf-a7520304"><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-oUbqx bgMQOP pf-10a75203"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-878a9d43"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-68866cca">As mentioned earlier, the FDA fully approved the use of Meloxicam for dogs. However, dog owners should still administer the drug responsibly.
<br>
<br>You shouldn't use Meloxicam in the following situations:
<br></span></p><ul data-pf-type="List" class="sc-pcLhl bMMcvF pf-ccb21147" style="--text-indent:0; --line-spacing:10px;"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-f013ba7b"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-6cca90a6"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Pets with bloody vomit&nbsp;</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-540e748f"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-90a61d1b"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Pets with kidney or liver conditions</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-8da2e7dd"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-1d1b8cd7"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Pets experiencing a loss of appetite.</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-454d01e4"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-8cd7b951"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Dehydrated pets</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-04fde6b0"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-b9517227"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Pets that are pregnant&nbsp;</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-6159ccb2"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-722730c3"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Pets younger than six months old</span><br></span></li></ul><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-6914fe3f"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-30c3245a">Also, Meloxicam may have adverse effects when used in conjunction with other drugs. Therefore, it is best to consult with your vet and disclose your pet's current medication.
<br>
<br>You should exercise caution when using Meloxicam with the following drugs:&nbsp;<br></span></p><ul data-pf-type="List" class="sc-pcLhl bMMcvF pf-c4413358" style="--text-indent:0; --line-spacing:10px;"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-680f5c61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-245a8d0b"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Certain antibiotics</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-2f91745f"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-8d0b9c6f"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Anesthetics</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-c17d1c6f"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-9c6f6703"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Anticoagulants</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-db461666"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-6703a2ef"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Diuretics</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-1dc7ba78"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-a2efd307"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Antifungals</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-4cb9c441"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-d3078510"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Immunosuppressive drugs&nbsp;</span><br></span></li></ul><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-30c33502"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-8510a752">Depending on your dog's situation, you and your vet may need to monitor your dog closely before and after the start of meloxicam usage. You will most likely have to monitor liver and kidney function and other signs of gastrointestinal ulceration.
<br>
<br>Veterinarians often require annual blood tests for dogs taking Meloxicam.
<br>&nbsp;<br></span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-container="true" class="sc-pZopv bjKdkd pf-b396aa6f" data-pf-type="Section"><div class="sc-pQQXS iWCqut" style="max-width: 1170px;"><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-08bfb396 pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg:15px; --pf-s-md:15px; --pf-s-sm:15px; --pf-s-xs:15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--undefined"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-df16c74c" data-pf-type="Column"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-9d54e5bd"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-04953eab">Meloxicam Dosage for Dogs<br></span></h2><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-oUbqx bgMQOP pf-a0df16c7"><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-oUbqx bgMQOP pf-aba0df16"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-6b3c602c"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-3eaba0df">You should always administer Meloxicam according to your veterinarian's instructions. 
<br>
<br>When in doubt, it would be best to use the lowest effective recommended dose. Typically, the recommended dosage of Meloxicam is around 0.09 milligrams per pound of your dog's body weight on the first day.
<br>
<br>All subsequent treatments are commonly administered once a day with a dosage of around 0.045 milligrams per pound of body weight.
<br>
<br>If your dog misses a dose of Meloxicam, be sure to administer it as soon as possible. If it is already almost time for the next dose, simply skip the missed dose and continue with the prescribed schedule. Under no circumstances should you give your pet two doses of Meloxicam at once.&nbsp;<br></span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-container="true" class="sc-pZopv bjKdkd pf-71dd6466" data-pf-type="Section"><div class="sc-pQQXS iWCqut" style="max-width: 1170px;"><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-a84871dd pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg:15px; --pf-s-md:15px; --pf-s-sm:15px; --pf-s-xs:15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--undefined"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-cdf675f5" data-pf-type="Column"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-696c50e1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-c74ca265">How Much Does Meloxicam Cost?<br></span></h2><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-oUbqx bgMQOP pf-4fcdf675"><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-oUbqx bgMQOP pf-654fcdf6"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-accdd28e"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-a2654fcd">If you're looking for the cheapest option, you can easily find generic Meloxicam at an affordable price of around 50c per tablet. Be sure, however, that you are making your purchase from a reputable supplier.&nbsp;<br></span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-container="true" class="sc-pZopv bjKdkd pf-ce7d28f5" data-pf-type="Section"><div class="sc-pQQXS iWCqut" style="max-width: 1170px;"><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-23e6ce7d pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg:15px; --pf-s-md:15px; --pf-s-sm:15px; --pf-s-xs:15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--undefined"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-06b5616c" data-pf-type="Column"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-f0fb6b37"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-75f5684e">Side Effects of Meloxicam<br></span></h2><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-oUbqx bgMQOP pf-5c06b561"><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-oUbqx bgMQOP pf-915c06b5"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-ab391b76"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-684e53ea">Almost all side effects associated with meloxicam use in dogs involve gastrointestinal upset, similar to all other NSAID medications. If symptoms persist or worsen, however, you should contact your veterinarian immediately. They may want to adjust the dosage or prescribe an alternative treatment.<br><br>Common side effects associated with Meloxicam include:<br></span></p><ul data-pf-type="List" class="sc-pcLhl bMMcvF pf-497ddbe7" style="--text-indent:0; --line-spacing:10px;"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-5e8f6bfe"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-53eadb30"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Black or bloody diarrhea</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-3cd50742"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-db3092c1"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Bloody vomit</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-4c3f7178"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-92c171d9"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Weight gain</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-7452561a"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-71d9e969"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Increased thirst</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-35939941"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-e969b9dd"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Fatigue</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-a733fb05"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-b9dd6bbb"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Jaundice</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-682eaaab"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-6bbb33ad"><span style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration-line: underline;"><a href="https://www.relievet.com/blogs/tips/home-remedies-for-dogs-with-skin-allergies-itchy">Itchiness</a></span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-435b38a9"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-33ad3d63"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Abdominal discomfort</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-ff6f497d"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-3d63db91"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Behavioral changes</span><br></span></li></ul><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-be66ccfb"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-db915c06">As with most medications, there is a risk of your dog having an allergic reaction that may lead to anaphylaxis. If you see any signs of an allergic reaction, be sure to contact your vet immediately.<br></span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-container="true" class="sc-pZopv bjKdkd pf-f37953cf" data-pf-type="Section"><div class="sc-pQQXS iWCqut" style="max-width: 1170px;"><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-9b701ac4 pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg:15px; --pf-s-md:15px; --pf-s-sm:15px; --pf-s-xs:15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-9bf37953" data-pf-type="Column"><div data-pf-type="Form2" class="sc-qQAox csiTZj pf-fb5f899b">{% form 'customer' %}<div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-019bf379 pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg:10px; --pf-s-md:15px; --pf-s-sm:15px; --pf-s-xs:15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-6cc36d01" data-pf-type="Column"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-36870ca5"><span data-pf-type="T