ur submissions!</p>{% endif %}{% endform %}</div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-container="true" class="sc-pZopv bjKdkd pf-d37755a8" data-pf-type="Section"><div class="sc-pQQXS iWCqut" style="max-width: 1170px;"><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-ea9fd377 pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg:15px; --pf-s-md:15px; --pf-s-sm:15px; --pf-s-xs:15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--undefined"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-9ba33029" data-pf-type="Column"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-15d91d03"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-53cf2711">Natural Alternatives<br></span></h2><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-oUbqx bgMQOP pf-809ba330"><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-oUbqx bgMQOP pf-f9809ba3"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-db03a293"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-27112744">A few notable Chinese herbal formulas known to help with arthritis in dogs include:<br></span></p><ul data-pf-type="List" class="sc-pcLhl bMMcvF pf-5a67fcff" style="--text-indent:0; --line-spacing:10px;"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-9d404126"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-2744c2fd"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Ligusticum</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-53070c1f"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-c2fdeb9f"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Corydalis</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-fbd85a67"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-eb9f81f9"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Hindquarter weakness</span><br></span></li></ul><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-294a1669"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-81f9809b">Indian herbs such as Turmeric and <a href="https://www.relievet.com/blogs/tips/what-can-i-give-my-dog-for-pain#boswellia-for-dogs" style="text-decoration-line: underline;" target="_self">Boswellia </a>are also known to be effective anti-inflammatories. The same goes for the omega-3 fatty acids commonly found in flaxseed oil, sardines, and krill.
<br>
<br>Bone broth can also be given to your dog to serve as a natural preventative measure against Osteoarthritis. It helps your dog build his or her cartilage and protect his or her joints.
<br>
<br>Lastly, you may consider talking to your vet about&nbsp;<a href="https://www.relievet.com/products/cbd-oil-for-dogs" style="text-decoration-line: underline;" target="_self">CBD oil for dogs</a>. A study conducted in 2018 found that CBD oil has the potential to help dogs manage pain caused by Osteoarthritis. The study involved administering either a placebo or CBD for four weeks, twice daily.
<br>
<br>The study found that the dogs who received doses of CBD oil showed a significant decrease in the symptoms of pain associated with arthritis. These dogs became more active and experienced much less pain when compared to the dogs given placebos. 
<br>
<br>More research is needed to draw a complete conclusion on CBD oil for dogs with arthritis, but so far, it is very promising. 
<br>
<br>If you are interested in taking the route of natural and alternative treatments for your dog, such as the treatments listed above, you may consider consulting a holistic veterinarian who has experience dealing with natural or alternative remedies.
